[SN]TITLE[SN]
A12 crash victim's condition 'no longer life-threatening'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A woman critically injured when she was hit by a car on an Essex dual carriageway is "no longer in a life-threatening condition", police said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The woman sustained leg and head injuries on the A12 just south of Chelmsford, at 01:30 GMT on Boxing Day.
Essex Police said her condition after hospital treatment had "improved".
A 41-year-old man from Sevenoaks, Kent, arrested on suspicion of drinking and driving and causing grievous bodily harm, has been bailed until February.
